prompt:
Add a public function called SayHello to Effects.calr that prints a greeting to the console. It takes str parameter name and returns void. The function must declare the console write effect.

Use this exact Calor console write syntax:
§F{f001:SayHello:pub}
  §I{str:name}
  §O{void}
  §E{cw}
  §C{Console.WriteLine}
    §A name
  §/C
§/F{f001}

The §E{cw} declares the console write effect:
- cw = console write (Console.WriteLine, Console.Write, etc.)
- Functions with side effects MUST declare them
- The compiler enforces effect declarations
